<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-12-21T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-12-21T18:00:00-05:00" n="216" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d216">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">812.24/655a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morrow</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-12-21T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">December 21,
                                        1927—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>304. The Department would like to know if in your opinion this is the
                            opportune time to relax the present restrictions on the exportation to
                            Mexico of airplanes, munitions, and other supplies purchased by the
                            Government of Mexico and now held up in the United States. Your
                            suggestions will be appreciated.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>